%H A229709 Christopher Ambrose, <a href="http://www.integers-ejcnt.org/n55/n55.Abstract.html">On the Least Primitive Root Expressible as a Sum of Two Squares</a>, INTEGERS, Electronic J. of Combinatorial Number Theory, Vol. 13, Paper A55, 2013.
%e A229709 a(4) = 5 as 5 = 2^2 + 1^2 is a primitive root mod 7 (the 4th prime).
%o A229709 (SageMath) def A229709(n) : p = nth_prime(n); return next(i for i in PositiveIntegers() if i%p!=0 and mod(i,p).multiplicative_order() == p-1 and all(q%4 != 3 or e%2==0 for (q,e) in factor(i)))
